# Loop Engineering — Mandatory Execution Protocol

> **When:** Every plan step, every sprint task batch, every “mark ✅” claim.  
> **Parent:** [`execution-principles.mdc`](execution-principles.mdc) rule 17 · [`coding-skills.md`](coding-skills.md) Phase 3b  
> **Lesson:** Agents must not mark steps complete from memory — ground-check with Read/Grep/Glob each session ([`AGENT_LEARNINGS.md`](AGENT_LEARNINGS.md) #8).

---

## The loop (per plan step — do not batch)

```
READ → CONTRACT → PROPOSE → TEST → VERIFY → REPEAT/CHECKPOINT → SELF-REVIEW → (STOP or deliver)
```

| Phase | Agent must | Forbidden |
|-------|------------|-----------|
| **READ** | Run pre-state commands from the step VERIFY table (rg, Read, Glob). Record baseline. **No edits before READ completes.** | Coding before READ block written |
| **CONTRACT** | Paste step VERIFY table verbatim — pre-edit. | Internalizing intent without having the table open; treating VERIFY as post-hoc checklist; proposing edits without pasting the table |
| **PROPOSE** | Name files, symbols, expected post-state. **Scope must match CONTRACT rows only.** | Vague "will implement X"; proposing edits beyond CONTRACT scope |
| **TEST** | Implement. Read-before-edit. One edit per tool call. | Implementing N+1 while N unverified |
| **VERIFY** | **Re-paste the VERIFY table with every row annotated PASS or FAIL.** Include exit codes or `file:line` citations. **Same table as CONTRACT — commands re-run, results pasted.** Any FAIL → return to TEST; do not advance. | Citing results conversationally without a structured record; ✅ from diff memory or prior turn |
| **REPEAT/CHECKPOINT** | All rows PASS → print §4 checkpoint with Status SHIPPED, PARTIAL, or BLOCKED. | Advance to next step with any FAIL row; skip checkpoint output |
| **SELF-REVIEW** | Before delivering SHIPPED/PARTIAL/BLOCKED: run §1b self-audit. If any audit item fails, return to VERIFY or TEST. **Do not** end with a passive "ready for next step?" — answer §1b questions in the deliverable. | Delivering without self-audit; no follow-up question |
| **STOP or deliver** | **STOP** if SELF-REVIEW finds gaps, scope creep, or unresolved human decisions. **Deliver** checkpoint + §1b block only when audit passes or PARTIAL/BLOCKED is honestly documented. | Ship-and-pray; passive handoff without audit trail |

**Hard rule:** No step is **SHIPPED** until VERIFY evidence table is all ✅.  
**Hard rule:** No phase is **complete** while any step lacks SHIPPED + evidence.  
**Hard rule:** If a plan step has no concrete VERIFY command (grep pattern, file:line read, test with expected exit code), the step is **BLOCKED**. Do not implement steps with missing VERIFY lines — flag them to the user first.

### Forbidden in any phase

| Action | Why |
|--------|-----|
| PROPOSE or edit without CONTRACT paste | VERIFY table never governed the edit sequence |
| VERIFY as conversational summary only ("tests pass, looks good") | Reviewer cannot audit — no structured record |
| SHIPPED without checkpoint table | No session evidence per § Checkpoint table |
| Advance to step N+1 with any FAIL row | Violates § Plan VERIFY Contract item 4 |
| Intent internalized without CONTRACT paste | Agent fills in VERIFY after code is written — post-hoc checklist |
| SHIPPED without SELF-REVIEW block | §1b — no deliverable audit trail |
| Passive "ready for next step?" without §1b answers | Executor must self-audit first |

### Completion vocabulary (mandatory)

| Agent MAY say | When |
|---------------|------|
| **SHIPPED** | One plan step; that step's CONTRACT table is 100% PASS |
| **PARTIAL @ `<hash>`** | Step scope done; ≥1 CONTRACT row FAIL or deferred |
| **BLOCKED** | Cannot complete VERIFY; missing table; command fails |

**Forbidden in any message:**
- "programme complete", "054 closed", "all done", "gate passed"
- These require a separate Programme Close VERIFY packet — never inferred from child SHIPPED

**Forbidden excuses for PASS:**
- exit 0 with 0 tests executed
- "spec not created" when `Glob **/*Spec*` finds a file
- "logged as open issue" on a CONTRACT row (that row = FAIL → PARTIAL or BLOCKED)

**False PASS on a CONTRACT row** → Status BLOCKED; step not approved.
**Bonus row marked PASS while CONTRACT row FAIL** → entire checkpoint invalid; re-run VERIFY.
**"Programme complete" without index VERIFY table** → reject; not SHIPPED.

