## 1b. SELF-REVIEW (mandatory before deliver)

After VERIFY and before the final message, the executor **asks itself** (not the human) and records answers **in the deliverable**, directly under the checkpoint.

| # | Self-audit question | Pass when |
|---|---------------------|-----------|
| 1 | Did I verify **every CONTRACT row** with evidence from **this session** (exit codes, `path:line`, test counts)? | Yes for each row, or row marked FAIL with reason |
| 2 | What **question do I have for the human** before the next step? | Listed explicitly, or **"None"** |
| 3 | What is **unclear** that the next step needs? | Listed explicitly, or **"None"** |

### Deliverable format (append after checkpoint Status)

```markdown
### SELF-REVIEW — Plan NNN Step X
| # | Question | Answer |
|---|----------|--------|
| 1 | Every CONTRACT row verified with session evidence? | [Yes / No — if No, do not deliver SHIPPED] |
| 2 | Human question before next step? | [question or None] |
| 3 | Unclear for next step? | [item or None] |

**Deliver decision:** STOP | DELIVER SHIPPED | DELIVER PARTIAL | DELIVER BLOCKED
```

### Forbidden (SELF-REVIEW)

| Action | Why |
|--------|-----|
| SHIPPED without SELF-REVIEW block | Human cannot audit executor discipline |
| "Ready for next step?" as the only closing line | Passive handoff — §1b must be answered first |
| Skipping human questions when scope/plan ambiguity exists | Next session starts blind |
| Delivering SHIPPED when self-audit #1 is No | CONTRACT not actually met |

