## JSX Relocate Protocol (layout steps)

For plan steps tagged **relocate, grid, wrap,** or **layout** (see `plan-standards.mdc` §3d):

```
READ (inventory) → PROPOSE (delete list + insert list) → TEST (delete then insert) → VERIFY (mount counts) → REPEAT
```

| Phase | Agent must | Forbidden |
|-------|------------|-----------|
| **READ** | `rg` every component; count pre-state mount occurrences | Skipping mount counts |
| **PROPOSE** | Delete list (component, line) + insert list (component, target, line) | Vague "move card to grid" |
| **TEST** | Delete first, then insert | Insert-then-delete (leaves duplicates) |
| **VERIFY** | Mount-count table — pre vs post per component | tsc/vitest as sole evidence |

#### Required VERIFY output for layout steps

```markdown
### Step X.Y — VERIFY (layout)
| Component | Pre count | Post count | Pass when | Pass |
|-----------|-----------|------------|-----------|:----:|
| FxReconciliationCard | 1 | 2 | exactly 1 | ❌ — remove duplicate at L1020 |
| MobileFAB | 0 | 1 | exactly 1 | ✅ |
```

**Hard rule:** Post-state mount count greater than Pass-when is VERIFY ❌ — fix before next step, even if tsc and vitest pass.

